Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from
greens. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a small #pot over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites
and cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{1%minute}. Season with @salt{}.

Stir @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} into pot with scallion whites. Add ¾ cup water
(1 1/2 cups for 4 servings) and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off
heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, zest and quarter @lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest 1 lemon and quarter
both). Trim ends from @zucchini{1}. Using a #peeler and working over a large #bowl,
shave zucchini lengthwise into ribbons, rotating as you go. Stop once you get to the
seedy core; discard core.

Toss zucchini ribbons with @basil oil{5%tsp} and half the lemon zest. Season with
plenty of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a squeeze of lemon juice to taste; toss to coat.
Set aside. Rinse @shrimp{10%oz}, then pat dry with #paper towels{} and season all over
with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings)
in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; sprinkle with
a pinch of @?chili flakes{1%tsp} if desired. Cook, stirring, until opaque and cooked
through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Meanwhile, place @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) in a small
microwave-safe #bowl; microwave until melted, ~{1%minute}. Squeeze in juice from
1 lemon wedge (2 wedges for 4). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; stir to combine.

Fluff rice with a #fork and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; divide between
#plates{}. Shake off any excess marinade from zucchini ribbons, then arrange over rice.
Top with shrimp and drizzle with lemon butter. Garnish with scallion greens, remaining
lemon zest, and chili flakes to taste. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.